<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="317" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1361,2034]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,324,1361,1386]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
<typeStatus box="[151,210,1361,1386]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Type</typeStatus>
material.
</emphasis>
In a recent attempt to examine the 
<typeStatus box="[717,765,1362,1385]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">type</typeStatus>
specimen of this species, we learned that the 
<collectionCode box="[1275,1336,1362,1385]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34880" name="Peabody Museum of Natural History" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">YPM</collectionCode>
does not have the 
<typeStatus box="[253,312,1398,1422]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">types</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Petrunkevitch" authorityYear="1925" box="[351,547,1397,1422]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="longithorax">
<emphasis box="[351,547,1397,1422]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Mica longithorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(R. Pupedis, L. Munstermann, pers. comm.). Thus, this 
<typeStatus box="[1184,1232,1398,1422]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">type</typeStatus>
is considered lost (article 75.3.4 of 
<collectionCode box="[344,414,1434,1458]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">ICZN</collectionCode>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1361,2034]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1703280295" collectingDate="2008-09-26" collectionCode="ICZN" collectorName="Zhang &amp; G. B. Edwards &amp; Spencer Entomological Collection" country="Panama" latitude="9.40441" location="Toro" longLatPrecision="1" longitude="-82.3261" municipality="Bocas" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" specimenCount="4" stateProvince="British Columbia" typeStatus="neotype">
