<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1361,2034]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
The neotype was chosen based on the proximity to the type locality and comparisons of this specimen with the original description (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Petrunkevitch" box="[444,671,1721,1746]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" refString="Petrunkevitch, A. (1925) Arachnida from Panama. Transactions of the Connecticut Academy of Arts and Sciences, 27, 51 - 248." type="journal article" year="1925">Petrunkevitch 1925</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 155; compare with our 
<figureCitation box="[1019,1126,1721,1746]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1653,1675]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1631]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,195,1631]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 14. Hyetussa longithorax comb. nov. A female neotype, dorsal; B same, lateral; C same, ventral; D epigyne, ventral view; E same, cleared, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3098068/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Fig. 14D</figureCitation>
; ICZN articles 75.3.2 and 75.3.5).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1419,1793,1818]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1361,2034]" box="[199,1419,1793,1818]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1793,1818]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Females differ from all known species of this genus in having a reduced spination (
<date box="[1260,1288,1793,1818]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">v2</date>
di) on leg I.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="318" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1361,2034]" box="[199,544,1829,1854]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,419,1829,1854]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1361,2034]" lastBlockId="17.[151,1437,151,357]" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="318" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,412,1865,1890]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
Female (
<typeStatus box="[301,399,1865,1890]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">neotype</typeStatus>
).
</emphasis>
Total length: 2.80. Carapace 1.23 long, 0.77 wide, 0.46 high. Ocular quadrangle 0.65 long. Anterior eye row 0.65 wide and posterior 0.69 wide. Chelicera paturon with one promarginal and one retromarginal tooth, the promarginal with three cusps, the middle one largest, and the retromarginal with one curved cusp. Length of femur: I 0.55, II 0.44, III 0.49, IV 0.70; patella + tibia: I 0.64, II 0.55, III 0.56, IV 0.83; metatarsus + tarsus: I 0.53, II 0.49, III 0.60, IV 0.73. Leg formula: 4132. Leg spination: femur I‒IV 0; patella I‒IV 0; tibia I‒IV 0; metatarsus I 
<date box="[306,336,151,176]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">v2</date>
di; II‒IV 0. Epigyne (
<figureCitation box="[599,774,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1653,1675]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1631]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,195,1631]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 14. Hyetussa longithorax comb. nov. A female neotype, dorsal; B same, lateral; C same, ventral; D epigyne, ventral view; E same, cleared, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3098068/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Figs 14D‒14E</figureCitation>
): posterior edge bilobed, copulatory openings anteriorly placed. Color in alcohol: carapace brown with a tuft of white scales behind PLE, dark striation on the thoracic region and posterior borders with tufts of white scales, abdomen dorsum with three tufts of white scales anteriorly placed, middle of the abdomen with a pair of tufts of white scales on the sides, end of abdomen with a pair of tufts of white scales near to anal tubercle, venter of the abdomen brown, spinnerets brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
